================================================================================
Note on third-party runtime dependencies
================================================================================

This project does NOT redistribute any of the following tools. The bootstrap
scripts under `scripts/` download them at runtime to the user's local machine.
When you use those tools via this project, you are bound by their own
licenses, not this MIT License. The project author makes no warranty about
compatibility between your use case and the upstream license terms — read
them directly if it matters for your situation.

- yhaplo (https://github.com/23andMe/yhaplo) — non-commercial academic research
  use only. Bundles the ISOGG 2016 Y-chromosome tree.
- Beagle 5.4 (https://faculty.washington.edu/browning/beagle/beagle.html) —
  distributed under GNU General Public License v3 (GPL-3).
- HaploGrep3 (https://github.com/genepi/haplogrep3) — MIT License. Bundles
  PhyloTree 17.2.
- Temurin JDK 21 (https://adoptium.net/) — GPLv2 with Classpath Exception.

Public reference data downloaded by this project (1000 Genomes Project,
PGS Catalog, NCBI rCRS, PhyloTree, ISOGG) is in the public domain or under
permissive re-use licenses from the respective data consortia. See their
respective websites for details.

Curated data files shipped with this project (under `reference/carrier_panels/`
and `reference/curated_snps.tsv`) are original compilations distilled from
public sources (ClinVar, ClinGen, CFTR2.org, ACMG guidelines, PGS Catalog).
These TSVs are licensed under the same MIT terms as the project code.
